<item>
            <title>[LU-19551] Return error when setting default quota on nodemap with offsets</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19551</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a client is associated with a nodemap that has offsets defined, the nodemap maps the PROJID and UID for ID 0 to the offset (depending on the offset, it may also be squashed). A root user of such a nodemap can attempt to set the default quota (ID 0) but it is actually offset. Therefore, a command, e.g., &quot;lfs setquota -P -b 10G -B 10G -i 100K -I 100K /mnt/lustre&quot; succeeds but it does not set the default quota (ID 0) (since the PROJID is offset to a non-zero value).&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The expected behavior should be that only root users of privileged nodemaps (admin=1,trusted=1, and no offsets) should be able to set the default quota. Otherwise, return a corresponding errorcode.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
